User: "How can I assign value to a particular row and column position in dataframe?"
Gideon: Below is the code recommendation for your ask!

import pandas as pd

df = pd.DataFrame(index=['A','B','C'], columns=['x','y'])
Output:
    x    y
A  NaN  NaN
B  NaN  NaN
C  NaN  NaN

df.at['C', 'x'] = 10
Output:
    x	 y
A	NaN	NaN
B	NaN	NaN
C	10	NaN

